<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANTI-CIGARETTE DECISIONS AND SMOKING BANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Braude law has little to do with smoking in restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
It is easy to find restaurants with little or no smoking. The Braudes of the 
world didn't do that with their regulations. People did it all by their little 
selves. 
</P>
<P>
The Braude rule is about the degree to which governments more and more 
micro-manage businesses and the lives of people. 
</P>
<P>
Look in Braude's jacket pocket. I'll bet you'll find his draft of a law 
regulating which side of the street smokers may walk on. His restrictions 
belong in the ashtray. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN C. HASSETT 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
