<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY OVER FEDERAL FUNDS FOR ARTISTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I continually read about the indignant taxpayer complaining about his/her tax 
"dollars" being wasted on "obscene" art. 
</P>
<P>
To get a grasp of the global picture look at these figures on per capita 
government spending on the arts by various nations in 1989: 
</P>
<P>
* $38.80 in West Germany; $24.91 in Sweden; $19.99 in Norway; $16.51 in the 
Netherlands; $15.48 in Austria; $12.37 in France; $11.80 in Denmark; $7.74 in 
the United Kingdom, and 64 cents in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
E.W. SCHOYER 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
