<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CHESNOKOV OVERCOMES RAIN, VAN RENSBURG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Andrei Chesnokov of the Soviet Union outlasted the rain and Christo van 
Rensburg of South Africa, 6-2, 4-6, 6-2, Friday and moved into the 
quarterfinals of the WCT Tournament of Champions at New York. 
</P>
<P>
The second-round match began Thursday before rain washed out play on the hard 
courts at the West Side Tennis Club. At that time, Chesnokov led, 6-2, 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Chesnokov and Van Rensburg took turns posting streaks in between 
frequent showers that interrupted play and sent the final second-round match to 
an indoor court in Bethpage, N.Y., 26 miles from Forest Hills. 
</P>
<P>
In another second-round match, Aaron Krickstein outlasted Petr Korda of 
Czechoslovakia, 4-6, 6-3, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
In the only quarterfinal match completed Friday, Emilio Sanchez of Spain 
defeated Patrick McEnroe, 6-3, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
Henri Leconte of France wasted three match points in his battle against Todd 
Martin of Lansing, Mich., before a heavy mist made the courts too slippery, and 
play was suspended for the night. 
</P>
<P>
John McEnroe overcame six hours of rain delays to upset third-seeded Brad 
Gilbert, 6-3, 6-2, in the quarterfinals of the $250,000 Hamlet Challenge Cup at 
Commack, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
In another quarterfinal match, Guy Forget of France, seeded eighth, eliminated 
second-seeded Andres Gomez of Ecuador, 6-7 (7-4), 6-0, 7-5. The second set 
lasted only 21 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
The matches of Stefan Edberg-Jonas Svensson and Pete Sampras-Goran Ivanisevic, 
delayed by the weather, will conclude today. 
</P>
<P>
An ankle injury forced second-seeded Raffaella Reggi of Italy to retire from 
her quarterfinal match with unseeded Mercedes Paz of Argentina in a $225,000 
tournament at Schenectady, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
Paz led Reggi, 6-1, 4-0, when the injury occurred. 
</P>
<P>
Another quarterfinal match between Sylvia Hanika of West Germany and Anke Huber 
was shortened by injury when Hanika hurt her elbow and had to retire in the 
third set, which was tied at 2-2. Hanika won the first set, 6-4, but lost the 
second, 6-7. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarterfinals of the $160,000 women's tournament at Mahwah, N.J., Leila 
Meskhi of the Soviet Union upset fourth-seeded Katerina Maleeva of Bulgaria, 
6-2, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Meskhi's ground strokes forced Maleeva to commit numerous errors in the match 
that was forced indoors after being delayed by rain. 
</P>
<P>
Meskhi will face top-seeded Steffi Graf in the semifinals today. Also, 
second-seeded Zina Garrison will third-seeded Jennifer Capriati. 
</P>
<P>
Rain postponed second-round qualifying for the U.S. Open at New York. It was 
rescheduled for today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
