<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOOKING FOR A SIGN OF HOPE FROM RAIDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We realize the Raiders did not have a great year last year, but after watching 
all the games that were shown on television, it was clear that Steve Beuerlein 
outplayed Jay Schroeder. 
</P>
<P>
I've talked to many football fans, and we are all confused as to why Schroeder 
was signed immediately and Beuerlein still hasn't signed for a smaller amount. 
There is probably some explanation for this and, as a Raider fan, I would 
appreciate knowing. 
</P>
<P>
HOWARD C. GULICK 
</P>
<P>
Ontario 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
