<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOW'S ON WAY OUT BECAUSE OF HIMSELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How like Eric Show, the ultimate antithesis of a team player, to carp and whine 
just as the Padres finally begin coming together as a team. He's angry the 
Padres "don't believe in him" and cites contract issues, Pat Dobson and 
probably Chub Feeney as the reasons for his demotion to the bullpen -- 
disregarding his astronomical 6.25 ERA. 
</P>
<P>
After all, this is the man who sat and sulked "why me?" as Pete Rose made a 
sports trivia answer. 
</P>
<P>
So Show wants a trade, and even his agent can't find an interested team. The 
reason? A team plot against him in the front office. A pitching coach who has 
turned around the careers of many (ask Mark Davis) who inexplicably hates Show. 
Remember folks, Eric Show is a John Bircher, familiar with seeing conspiracies 
and placing responsibilities and blame for one's fate on others. He has 
forgotten that to be respected as a man requires him to act like one. I won't 
be the only one glad to see him go. 
</P>
<P>
JASON BRADY 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
