<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES AT THE BOWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On Aug. 17 a very positive production of "An Old Fashioned Night at the Movies" 
was staged at the Hollywood Bowl. It was obviously fun for the sellout crowd to 
share in the movie-and-live-show concept. 
</P>
<P>
I feel forced to address the mean-spirited, "bah, humbug" attitude of Kevin 
Thomas' review. 
</P>
<P>
He dismisses the need for any live entertainment, and particularly zings the 
Doc Severinsen Tonight Show Band. Our band sounded particularly good that night 
and was anything but "off form," as suggested by Scrooge Thomas. His obvious 
annoyance at the rather long program clogged his ear and his judgment canals. 
</P>
<P>
We hope there will be more shows like it, and if Thomas stays away from musical 
critiques, I promise not to write any movie reviews. 
</P>
<P>
ED SHAUGHNESSY 
</P>
<P>
Tonight Show Band, NBC 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 
</P>
