<P>
GAS MASK FACTORY WORKING 24 HOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BARCELONA, Spain 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The heavy demand for gas masks from Middle Eastern distributors has forced a 
Barcelona firm to cut short vacations and begin round-the-clock production, one 
of the firm's owners says. 
</P>
<P>
Jeroni Llorca of Llorca Protective Systems said Thursday the company had 
planned to start producing its new Vispro civilian-use gas mask in September. 
But frantic calls from distributors in Saudi Arabia, Jordan, Syria and Israel 
persuaded the firm to begin immediately. 
</P>
<P>
Llorca said employees are producing about 1,500 masks a day. He expects his 
first shipment to go out Sept. 15. 
</P>
