<TEXT>
<P>
An investigation into reports of brutality and corruption in a special police 
force that patrols Oakland's low-income housing projects has resulted in 
federal civil rights charges against a supervisor and five officers. A federal 
grand jury indicted the Oakland Housing Authority Police officers on criminal 
charges of conspiring to violate the rights of 14 people -- including three 
