<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE ARREST 2 AFTER COCAINE SEIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Narcotic investigators with the Ventura County Sheriff's Department arrested 
two Los Angeles men Thursday after finding five kilograms of cocaine and 
$20,000 cash under the back seat of their car, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Roberto Camacho Espinosa and Loreto Chaidez Mendoza, both 30, were being held 
in Ventura County Jail on suspicion of possessing narcotics for sale, said Sgt. 
Robert Sparks. 
</P>
<P>
Bail has been set at $100,000 each. 
</P>
<P>
On a tip from the Drug Enforcement Administration in Santa Barbara, 
investigators arranged to meet the men for an undercover buy in Thousand Oaks, 
said Lt. Guy Inglis. 
</P>
<P>
But the two men left the parking lot at Du Par's Restaurants &amp; Bakeries, 33 
W. Thousand Oaks Blvd., before investigators arrived, he said. 
</P>
<P>
About 13 narcotics investigators searched for the car on the Ventura Freeway 
before pulling over the suspects at Balboa Avenue in Encino about 5:30 p.m., he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators found the cocaine, valued at about $125,000, and $20,000 in small 
bills under the car's back seat and a loaded .45-caliber automatic handgun 
under the front seat, Inglis said. KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
