<P>
Stock Exchanges Set Up Formal Ties: The Pacific Stock Exchange and the Taiwan 
Stock Exchange announced that they have set up formal links by becoming "sister 
exchanges," the first such agreement between American and Asian trading 
centers. Leopold Korins, chairman and chief executive of the PSE, said the pact 
is designed to produce expanded investment opportunities for investors in both 
countries and to improve the settlement and regulatory capabilities of both 
exchanges. 
